A Manchester United supporters' group is planning to entice Cristiano Ronaldo back to the club by flying over a 'COME HOME RONALDO' banner during their hero's next La Liga game.

United Reel, which includes members from all over the world, has called for donations to help fund the fly-by plea, which is due to take place midway through the Real Madrid superstar's match against Villarreal at the Estadio El Madrigal on Saturday.

The group has teamed up with affiliated supporters' clubs - MUSC United Arab Emirates, MUSC Lebanon and MUSC Egypt - to show their former player 'how much the United faithful still love and support him'.

