A package of around £120m would be needed to bring Ronaldo back to Old Trafford, something which may be too much for United with the prospect of Radamel Falcao signing permanently next summer.

However, the 29-year-old appeared to dismiss the notion of a return after his latest starring performance in scoring four goals during Real Madrid's 5-1 victory over Elche on Tuesday.

'They are all speculations about my future ... My future is Madrid. I'm happy this season is going well and my future, I will not speak about, it does not make sense,' he said.

